messages.message: Whoops, sorry everyone, just saw these messages. Yes, I renamed apps-vendor.bundle.js to vendor.bundle.js.
@Kerry let me know if you want to jump on a call to debug

and yes, the end goal is to bundle at deployment time only and have webpack devserver be the default locally. the steps I'm taking to get there are laid out here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xH2ppbxjDKfhF05Jd-Q_mFK5DdF1KOZ5YMJ-Qq1punI/edit
@Ashish our biggest money spend on AWS is RDS (because we run multi-zone availability) -- it's not a bad idea to explore this: https://aws.amazon.com/rds/aurora/serverless/
never mind -- this is unpredictable and not useful -- we should continue to use what we have
this can be useful for development instance/testing
